WEBVTT

00:00.674 --> 00:03.739
Thank you for downloading or streaming this message from Immanuel Church.

00:04.160 --> 00:08.648
We are one church with multiple locations, and we believe God wants to bless you right where you are.

00:08.688 --> 00:14.799
In a few moments, you're going to hear some practical teaching from God's Word that I believe will be inspiring and relevant to your life.

00:15.560 --> 00:25.458
First, though, if you haven't yet experienced Immanuel Live, we encourage you to go to our website, eclive.org, to check out our service times and locations so that you can experience Immanuel in person

00:25.538 --> 00:26.760
or through our online campus.

00:27.461 --> 00:36.233
If this message blesses you and you'd like to support the ministry financially, again, you can go to eclive.org and click on the giving tab and choose online campus at your campus.

00:36.914 --> 00:41.400
Thanks again for joining us today and we hope this message will be an encouragement to you on your spiritual journey.

00:42.782 --> 00:44.624
It is so good to be here today with you.

00:45.305 --> 00:47.969
Brand new series today.

00:48.089 --> 00:50.212
I get fired up and we got some new content.

00:50.673 --> 00:52.135
Okay, it's February.

00:52.676 --> 00:54.418
Guess what's in February?

00:54.978 --> 00:56.901
Valentine's Day, okay?

00:56.921 --> 01:04.152
So we like to talk about romance, we like to talk about relationships around this time of the year to kind of help everybody out.

01:04.613 --> 01:07.317
And so the title of this series is called Ground Rules.

01:07.337 --> 01:12.165
You know, when I was growing up, I was blessed to have two older brothers that were right in front of me.

01:12.325 --> 01:15.370
I'm 42, my brother Jason's 43, my brother Jimmy's 44.

01:16.071 --> 01:19.877
My mother had three boys in diapers, okay?

01:19.897 --> 01:20.658
Can you imagine?

01:21.282 --> 01:25.288
You know, I mean, we broke everything in the house that belonged to my mom.

01:25.308 --> 01:27.091
Dishes, plates, vases.

01:27.171 --> 01:27.832
I mean, you name it.

01:27.852 --> 01:29.455
We broke it because of all the games we played.

01:29.475 --> 01:31.538
A lot of fun growing up with two older brothers that close.

01:32.099 --> 01:34.562
We also had a bunch of friends in the neighborhood that we lived.

01:34.582 --> 01:38.689
We would go out about every single day after homework or during the summer, for sure.

01:39.230 --> 01:41.513
And we would play all kinds of games together.

01:41.533 --> 01:44.458
And we had tons of kids in middle school and high school, our age.

01:44.978 --> 01:49.906
And in particular, during football season, which we're about ready to watch the Super Bowl here today in a little while,

01:50.018 --> 01:58.488
We would play lots of football, and we'd have anywhere from eight to 12 to 15, 14 kids, and we would quickly divide up.

01:58.508 --> 02:06.618
We had a field out back that we could play in, and we would divide up teams, and then the first thing that the two captains would do is they would set the ground rules.

02:06.698 --> 02:19.013
We had to put a hat or a sweatshirt to create this end zone or another hat and a sweatshirt to create this end zone, then we'd figure out where the sidelines were, and then we'd figure out how many completions you needed to get a first down.

02:19.073 --> 02:19.794
Anybody with me?

02:20.034 --> 02:20.515
Ever do this?

02:20.615 --> 02:20.855
Okay.

02:21.276 --> 02:22.018
Ladies, probably not.

02:22.038 --> 02:27.227
Maybe there's some tough ladies out there that played some soccer football, you know, with their friends growing up, or two hand touch or whatever.

02:27.628 --> 02:33.218
And then you'd have to create, you know, how many Mississippi before you rush the passer, one Mississippi, two Mississippi.

02:33.278 --> 02:33.979
Anybody remember that?

02:34.340 --> 02:36.905
It was different according to how many players you had on the other team.

02:36.965 --> 02:39.890
And so after we set all those ground rules,

02:40.386 --> 02:42.771
then we could actually have fun and play the game.

02:43.393 --> 02:49.687
But even without adults, these 12-year-olds, 13, 14-year-olds, we understood one fundamental idea.

02:49.747 --> 02:54.779
If we're gonna have fun, if we're gonna be able to play this game, we need to know what the ground rules are.

02:55.541 --> 02:57.846
I believe the same thing is true when it comes to relationships.

02:58.467 --> 02:59.730
I really do.

03:00.130 --> 03:01.231
What are the boundaries?

03:01.311 --> 03:02.213
What are the ground rules?

03:02.253 --> 03:05.236
Where's the areas that we can't cross?

03:05.417 --> 03:10.323
What are the rules here so that we can have this fun, healthy relationship?

03:10.343 --> 03:12.145
That's what this series is gonna be all about.

03:12.245 --> 03:18.573
What are those ground rules that I believe that God would say are the ground rules to have healthy relationships?

03:18.593 --> 03:20.295
We're gonna dive into that over the next three weeks.

03:20.315 --> 03:21.116
You excited about that?

03:21.537 --> 03:21.837
Yeah?

03:22.098 --> 03:22.959
All right, I'm glad.

03:22.979 --> 03:23.960
I'll be excited for you.

03:24.220 --> 03:25.682
I'm excited about it.

03:26.946 --> 03:28.088
Okay, who's this series for?

03:28.168 --> 03:32.858
This series is for anyone who is human because we are relational creatures.

03:33.700 --> 03:33.980
Okay?

03:34.782 --> 03:42.738
This series is specifically for anybody who wants to date somebody, is dating somebody, is engaged to somebody.

03:42.850 --> 03:50.661
wants to be engaged to somebody, wants to get married, is married, been married, divorce, wants to get remarried.

03:51.322 --> 03:56.749
Again, this is for all human beings because human beings are relational.

03:56.770 --> 04:02.337
Now, if you're sitting there there today, you're watching online and you're like, well, I don't wanna be in a romantic relationship, I'm just done.

04:02.578 --> 04:04.480
Well, you're still gonna have relationships, okay?

04:04.500 --> 04:11.410
You're gonna have roommates, you're gonna have people in your life, you're gonna have friends, even if it's platonic, and you never know, you never know, God might change your heart.

04:11.842 --> 04:18.730
And then you might meet somebody, so don't tune me out if you're not into romance, okay?

04:18.750 --> 04:21.293
Because this is very applicable for you as well.

04:21.333 --> 04:23.877
Two big tensions that come up when it comes to romance.

04:24.377 --> 04:26.099
The first one is for the single folks.

04:26.119 --> 04:26.980
It's in your notes there.

04:27.020 --> 04:27.761
You ready for it?

04:28.362 --> 04:31.306
How in the world am I gonna find the right person?

04:32.147 --> 04:33.388
Isn't that the big question?

04:33.468 --> 04:36.011
Where am I gonna find them in church?

04:36.171 --> 04:37.413
Am I gonna find their church?

04:37.493 --> 04:38.654
That's a good place to look.

04:38.694 --> 04:40.076
Am I gonna find them in college?

04:40.096 --> 04:41.618
Am I gonna find them in a bar?

04:41.986 --> 04:44.288
Am I going to find them down by the river living in a van?

04:44.408 --> 04:44.789
I don't know.

04:46.330 --> 04:47.471
Where am I going to find?

04:47.671 --> 04:49.693
That's not the right person, by the way.

04:52.236 --> 04:53.076
I don't know where that came from.

04:53.116 --> 04:53.397
Sorry.

04:56.239 --> 04:59.122
Where am I going to find the right person?

04:59.362 --> 05:05.788
Do you know that this is such a big tension in our lives that there's an entire billion dollar?

05:05.908 --> 05:06.789
I did say billion.

05:07.730 --> 05:11.954
There's an a billion dollar industry created around this

05:12.130 --> 05:13.792
one tension in this country.

05:13.832 --> 05:29.466
Today, dating services and dating apps collect $3 billion a year for people to pay for access to websites so they can look at pictures and bios and see if they can find the right person.

05:30.507 --> 05:38.915
Apps like Tinder and Match.com and OK, Cupid and Bumble and my favorite, my favorite, Plenty O Fish.

05:40.617 --> 05:41.938
That's an app.

05:43.042 --> 05:43.924
No, I don't use it.

05:44.104 --> 05:45.226
I just like the name of it.

05:46.348 --> 05:47.531
But it's a pretty good name.

05:48.072 --> 05:52.500
What about, this one tickles me, what about christianfarmers.com?

05:52.821 --> 05:53.763
Oh, don't you love it?

05:55.506 --> 05:56.468
It's so specific.

05:57.891 --> 06:01.378
There's testimonials on there and say you can, you're a Christian and you're a farmer.

06:01.438 --> 06:02.039
Yeah, we've got one.

06:02.059 --> 06:02.880
We've got a match for you.

06:04.804 --> 06:05.746
It's amazing.

06:06.274 --> 06:07.816
And I'm not knocking any of those.

06:07.877 --> 06:16.350
I'm just telling you that people are making money off of you because we so desire to find the right person.

06:16.430 --> 06:20.076
So we're going to talk about how to resolve this issue of finding the right person.

06:20.677 --> 06:26.186
Now, if you're already married, we're going to talk about the tension that you often live with, which is this one right here.

06:26.587 --> 06:27.769
How do I fix it?

06:28.149 --> 06:31.154
More specifically, how do I fix him?

06:31.330 --> 06:35.379
Or, more specifically, how do I fix her?

06:35.900 --> 06:37.183
Like, she's the problem.

06:37.363 --> 06:38.906
He's the, he's the problem.

06:39.668 --> 06:42.314
Nick, we're in this group of people, those of us who are married.

06:43.095 --> 06:50.070
We're in this group of people where we look back at the first group of people who are trying to find the right person, and we laugh at them, right?

06:50.110 --> 06:51.794
Because we are on the other end of

06:51.970 --> 06:56.475
finding the right person and we've discovered that the right person is messed up.

06:57.876 --> 07:01.060
Like we married the right person and they're still screwed up.

07:01.120 --> 07:09.689
Like they have lots of issues and they fooled us and now we're on the other end of marrying the right person and we're thinking maybe we should find a different right person, right?

07:10.330 --> 07:12.452
And we're saying, how do I fix it?

07:12.552 --> 07:13.553
How do I fix him?

07:13.613 --> 07:18.098
How do I fix her before I just give up and go on another search?

07:18.146 --> 07:28.397
Well, I believe I'm gonna share something with you today that is not popular, and you're not gonna find it a business plan around this idea, and you're not gonna find it in books about dating.

07:29.318 --> 07:43.232
It's not a popular concept, but I believe what I'm gonna share with you today in this ground rule number one, will resolve both tensions of how do I find the right person if I'm single, and then if I'm married, how do I fix the situation that I'm currently in?

07:43.653 --> 07:44.914
Are you ready for it?

07:45.442 --> 07:47.124
Do you have your pen in your hand?

07:47.705 --> 07:52.071
Are you like sitting on the edge of your seat with baited breath like, give it to me, Pastor Danny.

07:53.012 --> 07:53.273
Are you?

07:54.314 --> 07:55.776
I see I dream about stuff like this.

07:56.717 --> 07:58.760
These moments in time like, give it to me.

07:59.621 --> 08:00.322
Okay, okay.

08:00.342 --> 08:00.843
You ready for it?

08:00.863 --> 08:01.203
Here we go.

08:01.224 --> 08:01.384
Ready?

08:01.624 --> 08:02.445
Ground rule number one.

08:02.766 --> 08:04.268
You have to be the right person.

08:05.870 --> 08:14.802
Again, this is not a popular idea and you will not find this in dating books or, you know, business plans around this concept, but it is so true.

08:15.810 --> 08:16.311
Let me explain.

08:17.392 --> 08:18.414
Because some of you are like, what?

08:19.175 --> 08:21.038
That's gonna help me find the right person, be the right person.

08:21.158 --> 08:22.560
That's gonna help solve my marriage problems.

08:22.580 --> 08:24.183
Like, problem's not me, problem's him, dude.

08:25.665 --> 08:26.126
Let me explain.

08:26.166 --> 08:28.689
Right now, you are a kind of person.

08:29.030 --> 08:30.292
You have a soul.

08:30.913 --> 08:38.885
Upon death, our soul, or that intangible part of who we are, our mind, our spirit, our will, will leave our physical body.

08:39.065 --> 08:40.607
That's called death, okay?

08:41.869 --> 08:45.074
That soul, we haven't died yet, so it's inside of us.

08:45.538 --> 08:47.121
That soul has a shape.

08:47.161 --> 08:47.942
It has a form.

08:47.982 --> 08:48.763
It has a kind.

08:48.844 --> 08:50.386
It's a type of person.

08:50.446 --> 08:51.668
What type of person are you?

08:52.149 --> 08:52.750
Are you kind?

08:52.830 --> 08:53.331
Are you general?

08:53.411 --> 08:53.892
Are you mean?

08:53.972 --> 08:54.513
Are you angry?

08:54.593 --> 08:55.255
Are you racist?

08:55.295 --> 08:55.635
Are you not?

08:55.916 --> 08:56.296
I don't know.

08:56.577 --> 08:57.298
I don't know what kind.

08:57.318 --> 09:00.143
I'd have to become your friend to find out what kind of person you are.

09:00.664 --> 09:04.931
But the people closest to you know what kind or what type of person you are.

09:05.552 --> 09:05.993
Hang with me.

09:06.033 --> 09:06.674
Here's where I'm going.

09:08.002 --> 09:17.052
The type of person that you are, the kind of soul that has been formed inside of you up to this point in your life is of extreme importance.

09:17.893 --> 09:19.935
It is vitally important.

09:19.955 --> 09:20.796
How do I know that?

09:20.996 --> 09:22.678
Well, you just go apply for an apartment.

09:24.380 --> 09:25.321
I need an apartment.

09:25.401 --> 09:27.363
I'm gonna go fill out an application.

09:27.383 --> 09:29.405
What's the first thing that that landlord's gonna do?

09:30.907 --> 09:32.028
Can I see your references?

09:33.570 --> 09:35.953
I'm gonna run a background check.

09:35.973 --> 09:37.234
I'm gonna call your former

09:38.466 --> 09:39.007
Landlord.

09:39.907 --> 09:43.391
Because I need to find out if you're the kind of person that pays the what?

09:44.112 --> 09:44.892
The rent.

09:44.912 --> 09:48.156
I need to find out if you treated the last department well.

09:48.636 --> 09:52.059
What kind of condition did you punch holes in the wall?

09:52.940 --> 09:55.162
Did you leave the last pays place a mess?

09:55.182 --> 09:58.666
Because if you left the last place a mess, you're going to leave my place a mess.

09:58.686 --> 10:06.994
And if you were late on your rent, then you're going to be late on your... You see how important it is the kind of person that you are.

10:07.138 --> 10:09.150
You go fill out an application for a job.

10:09.291 --> 10:09.855
What do you have to do?

10:10.519 --> 10:11.666
You got to fill out your what?

10:11.874 --> 10:14.338
your references, because they're going to call your former boss.

10:14.498 --> 10:19.726
They're going to call your former employer, and they're going to say, what kind of employee was she?

10:19.746 --> 10:20.647
What kind?

10:20.668 --> 10:22.110
Did they have a positive attitude?

10:22.150 --> 10:23.692
Did they cause problems?

10:23.712 --> 10:24.594
Or were they helpful?

10:24.874 --> 10:25.715
Were they effective?

10:25.735 --> 10:26.416
Were they lazy?

10:27.538 --> 10:29.882
Because they don't want to take a risk on somebody.

10:30.923 --> 10:34.008
That's the wrong kind of person.

10:34.309 --> 10:37.493
We're going to watch the Super Bowl today, most of us, many of us.

10:38.174 --> 10:40.498
You know what NFL teams do during the draft?

10:40.674 --> 10:54.498
When they got all these collegiate athletes coming up that are superstars and they want to draft them into their organizations and pay them millions of dollars, did you know that NFL teams will go all the way back to these players' middle school coaches and teachers?

10:56.782 --> 10:57.964
And they'll ask these questions.

10:58.325 --> 11:01.330
What kind of kid was he in middle school?

11:02.274 --> 11:13.430
What kind of, we know he can perform on the football field, but we're about to put millions of dollars into this guy, and we need to know what kind of person the shape of his soul is.

11:13.871 --> 11:14.712
Is he a liar?

11:15.053 --> 11:15.874
Does he work hard?

11:15.914 --> 11:16.635
Is he lazy?

11:17.416 --> 11:20.501
Before we draft this player.

11:20.801 --> 11:23.806
How important is it to be the right kind of person?

11:24.126 --> 11:25.328
Vital, yeah?

11:25.348 --> 11:26.249
This is what Jesus taught.

11:26.389 --> 11:26.750
Watch this.

11:27.751 --> 11:29.554
Matthew chapter 12, verse 33.

11:29.762 --> 11:31.784
A tree is identified by its fruit.

11:31.984 --> 11:33.566
You want to know what kind of tree it is?

11:33.846 --> 11:34.287
Look at it.

11:34.327 --> 11:35.128
Look at its branches.

11:35.348 --> 11:36.349
Are there oranges on the tree?

11:36.369 --> 11:37.030
It's an orange tree.

11:37.050 --> 11:38.011
Are there bananas on the tree?

11:38.051 --> 11:38.732
It's a banana tree.

11:38.792 --> 11:39.673
Real deep stuff here.

11:43.577 --> 11:47.361
If the tree is good, if it's not infected with termites or a disease, guess what?

11:47.441 --> 11:49.964
The fruit on the branches will also be good.

11:50.404 --> 11:55.330
If the tree is bad, if it's infected, the fruit on the tree will be bad.

11:55.350 --> 11:58.013
And then he switches to you and he switches to me.

11:58.573 --> 11:59.154
Watch this.

12:00.002 --> 12:06.691
In the same way, a good person produces good things from the treasury of a good heart.

12:06.751 --> 12:12.599
In other words, a good person has lots of good fruit in their life because they have a good heart.

12:13.099 --> 12:18.647
It's not infected with selfishness or narcissism or greed or anger or loss.

12:18.707 --> 12:24.074
No, there's joy and there's peace and there's courage and there's love inside and so there's good fruit in their life.

12:25.756 --> 12:30.002
But an evil person produces evil things from the treasury

12:30.882 --> 12:34.747
of an evil heart.

12:34.767 --> 12:37.430
Jesus emphasized character.

12:39.553 --> 12:44.939
He was most concerned about who you are on the inside.

12:46.021 --> 12:52.048
Why is that so important when it comes to finding the right person or fixing your marriage?

12:52.068 --> 12:53.289
Well, let's talk about the first one.

12:56.694 --> 13:00.338
You are a person.

13:00.770 --> 13:04.976
And the kind of person you are is the kind of person you're going to attract.

13:06.038 --> 13:06.719
Have you noticed this?

13:07.520 --> 13:08.702
We attract who we are.

13:10.144 --> 13:14.470
The kind of fruit on our tree will attract the people who are looking for that fruit.

13:16.073 --> 13:17.655
Whether good or whether bad.

13:17.855 --> 13:25.266
And for the first time some of you are like, that's how I ended up with this man in my life.

13:25.922 --> 13:28.064
It was the fruit in my life that attracted him to me.

13:28.085 --> 13:30.587
That's how I ended up with this woman in my life.

13:31.629 --> 13:36.935
We attract who we are, which goes back to the importance of our character.

13:37.115 --> 13:43.102
It is so important because we draw the same kind of people into our life that we are ourselves.

13:43.362 --> 13:44.664
Andy Stanley tells a story.

13:45.365 --> 13:47.527
He's the pastor of North Point Community Church.

13:48.128 --> 13:53.394
He did a relationship series a couple of years ago, and he tells a story about how a young woman came forward and told him.

13:53.602 --> 13:55.845
told him about her own experience.

13:56.166 --> 14:05.360
She was in her 20s and one night she was at a party and she met a man, she thought it was the man of her dreams, and she's telling her mom to score, actually.

14:06.422 --> 14:13.432
And she says, mom, come home, mom, you're not gonna believe this, I met this incredible man, he's handsome, he's got a great job, and he's one of those Christians like you.

14:14.113 --> 14:22.386
Like he doesn't just say, he goes to church and he reads his Bible and his faith is really the central part of his life, and she's so excited to tell her mom about this man that she met.

14:23.202 --> 14:27.007
And she's going on and on and her mom was just listening, ironing a shirt, you know, just listening.

14:28.229 --> 14:35.459
She said her mom put the iron down and looked at her and said, honey, that's, that's exciting.

14:35.780 --> 14:38.023
I'm glad you met that man, but there's only one problem.

14:40.707 --> 14:44.091
A man like that is not looking for a girl like you.

14:47.576 --> 14:51.762
She said when her mom said that it was like someone punched her in the stomach, she said she had to take a knee

14:52.418 --> 14:56.845
And she started to weep because she realized this truth.

14:58.067 --> 15:00.391
We attract who we are.

15:00.491 --> 15:05.339
And a man like that is not looking for a girl like her.

15:06.361 --> 15:08.665
I explained it this way in your notes if you're a note taker today.

15:10.228 --> 15:10.869
Here's the truth.

15:11.450 --> 15:18.962
You will only look for people who are at your level of personal growth and spiritual growth.

15:20.866 --> 15:42.917
If you've done the hard work to overcome selfishness or narcissism or ego problem or bitterness or envy or insecurity, if you've done the hard work to battle through addictions and you have victory in your life and it's taken you time to work on the tree and your hearts finally becoming good and there's good fruit in your life and then you suddenly meet somebody who's cute.

15:42.997 --> 15:43.698
They've got some money.

15:44.960 --> 15:45.962
Maybe he's got a nice car.

15:47.404 --> 15:49.106
Maybe she has a nice shape, whatever.

15:51.042 --> 15:53.807
And then you're talking to them like, man, I'm attracted to you.

15:53.867 --> 16:00.237
But man, you're still hung up on like you got grudges and bitterness.

16:01.640 --> 16:04.164
There's some deep selfishness inside of you.

16:05.627 --> 16:09.774
That person's not attractive to you because you've moved past that in your notes.

16:09.794 --> 16:10.375
I wrote it like this.

16:11.056 --> 16:14.802
Your personal internal growth becomes your filter.

16:15.170 --> 16:19.979
Remember, I'm answering the question, how do I find the right person when you have to become the right person?

16:19.999 --> 16:23.024
Because your personal growth becomes your filter.

16:23.225 --> 16:28.795
And now you're able to, regardless of somebody's physical attraction, you're able to say, no, I'm not there.

16:28.895 --> 16:30.157
I was there 10 years ago.

16:30.398 --> 16:33.964
But if I get with you now, it's going to be sort of like running a rehab center.

16:34.025 --> 16:37.010
I'm going to be like dragging your butt all the way around, you know?

16:37.410 --> 16:39.192
And I'm not interested in running a rehab center.

16:39.252 --> 16:40.814
I want to date somebody and get married.

16:40.834 --> 16:44.980
Like, if I start dating you, it's going to be like entering into the Ministry of Counseling.

16:45.000 --> 16:46.001
I'm going to be like counselor.

16:46.041 --> 16:47.703
And I can't counsel you.

16:47.744 --> 16:48.805
I need to be your girlfriend.

16:48.825 --> 16:50.067
I need to be your boyfriend.

16:51.128 --> 16:53.932
Never marry a fix or upper, folks.

16:54.252 --> 16:55.293
That is wisdom.

16:55.353 --> 16:56.195
That is gold.

16:56.595 --> 16:58.157
Listen, do it with houses.

16:58.538 --> 17:00.580
Do it with other cars.

17:00.861 --> 17:01.542
Fix up things.

17:01.622 --> 17:04.946
Do not fix up a person, okay?

17:05.986 --> 17:14.970
So when you do the hard work of the personal growth, you are looking for someone who's either at that your level, a little bit ahead of you, or maybe just right under you.

17:14.990 --> 17:18.279
We attract who we are.

17:19.402 --> 17:21.106
Second thing I wrote is this.

17:21.442 --> 17:24.286
Number two, people at your level of growth will look for you.

17:24.506 --> 17:28.311
Because I know some people say, well that means I'm going to be looking for a long time.

17:28.532 --> 17:34.840
There's not many people out there that take their faith as serious as I do or read the Bible like I do or put Christ first in their life.

17:34.860 --> 17:37.143
Like there's not that many girls out there like that.

17:37.163 --> 17:39.046
There's not that many guys out there like that.

17:39.126 --> 17:40.468
Okay, fair, fine.

17:40.488 --> 17:40.988
But guess what?

17:41.008 --> 17:41.709
There are a few.

17:42.450 --> 17:43.131
And guess what?

17:43.151 --> 17:45.234
They're looking for you too.

17:45.442 --> 17:47.104
You just have to be patient.

17:47.464 --> 17:50.648
Listen, it's better to be with no one than to be with the wrong one.

17:50.809 --> 17:51.169
Hello?

17:51.249 --> 17:53.212
Somebody please write that down.

17:53.272 --> 17:57.397
It is better to be with no one than it is to be with the wrong one.

17:59.079 --> 18:00.380
You just have to be patient.

18:00.400 --> 18:01.842
You just have to wait this thing out.

18:02.102 --> 18:06.087
Trust me, they're looking for you as much as you're looking for them, and they don't want to settle.

18:06.248 --> 18:07.729
They don't want to lower their standards.

18:07.789 --> 18:09.391
Ladies are notorious for doing this.

18:09.712 --> 18:10.773
Listen, that's not coming for me.

18:10.793 --> 18:12.776
That's coming from another lady, because I'm not a lady.

18:12.796 --> 18:13.517
You know what I'm saying?

18:13.797 --> 18:14.738
I'm a dude.

18:15.362 --> 18:25.152
But ladies, ladies, coming from the late, you tend to lower your standards and you're thinking, is this, well, I'll just fix him.

18:26.092 --> 18:28.255
I know he's not where he needs to be.

18:28.475 --> 18:29.816
I know he's not spiritually mature.

18:30.056 --> 18:35.121
I know he's not gonna be the leader of the home, but there's not much out there, and I'd rather be with someone than not with somebody.

18:35.141 --> 18:37.063
Don't do it, don't do it.

18:37.684 --> 18:40.527
It's better to be alone than to be with the wrong person.

18:40.547 --> 18:42.008
Listen, this is how Jackie and I met.

18:42.408 --> 18:44.050
I'm not, no joke, this is serious stuff.

18:44.834 --> 18:45.775
This is our story.

18:45.815 --> 18:47.798
When in high school is a bone head, many of you know that.

18:47.818 --> 18:48.840
It wasn't a Christ follower.

18:49.301 --> 18:55.370
We got saved at 17 years old, still really much a bone head, not in learning how to treat women.

18:55.390 --> 19:02.801
And I was still attracting people who had my value system and it was all surface level stuff and based on physical appearance.

19:03.061 --> 19:05.325
And so I knew in my heart, I'm not ready to date.

19:05.465 --> 19:08.850
So my second year of college, I decided to do a dating fast.

19:09.378 --> 19:10.520
I'm like, I don't know how to do this.

19:10.881 --> 19:14.067
I need to make the tree good so that there's good fruit, so that I can attract the right person.

19:14.167 --> 19:15.590
I don't know why that was intuitive to me.

19:15.630 --> 19:16.191
It just was.

19:16.732 --> 19:19.778
So for two years at Liberty University, I didn't go on one date.

19:20.599 --> 19:22.804
And there's beautiful girls everywhere.

19:23.324 --> 19:25.469
They were like, it was like three girls to every one guy.

19:26.350 --> 19:29.176
And they're all, you know, like there, and they're loving Jesus.

19:29.236 --> 19:30.318
And I'm like, no, I'm not gonna do it.

19:30.338 --> 19:30.819
I'm not gonna do it.

19:30.939 --> 19:32.562
Two years, two years.

19:33.282 --> 19:35.592
Finally, my junior year of college, I'm like, OK, I'm ready.

19:35.753 --> 19:36.316
I'm ready to go.

19:36.396 --> 19:37.561
I feel like I've got some good fruit.

19:37.601 --> 19:41.438
I know how to respect a woman and treat a woman rightly in the right way.

19:41.920 --> 19:43.186
And so I see Jackie.

19:43.938 --> 19:48.926
And I noticed her, she's 5'11", she's gorgeous, and there's like, wow.

19:48.946 --> 19:52.752
And so we start to hang out in a group of friends so I can kind of get to know her in a circle.

19:53.153 --> 19:56.858
And then I ask her out, and so she kind of hymns and haws, and finally she gave in.

19:57.499 --> 19:59.523
She was on a dating fast too, but that's another story.

19:59.563 --> 20:06.674
And so on one of our first dates, when we were alone, I took her to Frizzoli's, man, I just wined and dined her.

20:08.002 --> 20:09.143
I was a college student.

20:09.183 --> 20:09.483
Come on.

20:09.503 --> 20:11.025
It was like seven bucks in my pocket.

20:11.505 --> 20:13.087
And so I'm driving her back to her dorm.

20:13.107 --> 20:14.828
And I just said, look, here's the deal with me.

20:15.229 --> 20:16.290
I've already been down.

20:16.370 --> 20:17.791
Lots of roads I shouldn't have been down.

20:17.911 --> 20:18.652
I've paid the price.

20:18.732 --> 20:20.614
I don't want to mess around with sex.

20:20.654 --> 20:22.235
I don't want to mess around with worldly stuff.

20:22.316 --> 20:24.858
I'm not interested in the world systems.

20:24.978 --> 20:26.219
I'm now a Christ follower.

20:26.259 --> 20:27.280
Christ is the center of my life.

20:27.661 --> 20:28.301
I want to serve him.

20:28.341 --> 20:28.982
I love the Bible.

20:29.022 --> 20:29.542
I love church.

20:29.582 --> 20:30.383
I want to honor.

20:30.483 --> 20:33.086
If we have kids, I want to raise them in a godly home.

20:33.126 --> 20:35.428
And I want to church is going to be a big part of our life.

20:35.448 --> 20:37.650
I just laid it out there for her because I didn't want to waste time.

20:38.146 --> 20:41.431
I don't wanna date somebody and they're not on the same level where I'm at, right?

20:41.831 --> 20:43.654
And so I just said, where are you?

20:44.315 --> 20:45.497
Here's where I'm at, where are you at?

20:45.978 --> 20:47.079
And I was using my filter.

20:47.580 --> 20:50.725
And I was hoping she would say, man, I'm right there with you.

20:50.885 --> 20:52.327
And so sure enough, she said, you know what?

20:52.708 --> 20:56.974
I've been down some paths and I believe what you're saying is true and I wanna honor Christ.

20:56.994 --> 20:59.317
So I came to Liberty, I wanna honor Christ with my life.

21:00.219 --> 21:03.584
And I was like, that night I wanted to ask her to marry me.

21:05.446 --> 21:07.890
I didn't, I didn't, but man, I felt it in my heart.

21:08.002 --> 21:10.045
I was like, we're here, we're here.

21:10.105 --> 21:17.214
And then we started to date, and sure enough, as we date, it's one thing to say something, and then it's another thing to live it.

21:17.234 --> 21:23.001
There's always evidence, and there's always fruit, and so I saw that she really meant it, and I meant it, and so I ended up asking her to marry me.

21:23.782 --> 21:33.554
What's interesting about that, and I have never shared this before, is that back in 1997, in the leaflet of her Bible, this is before we even met,

21:33.698 --> 21:34.639
This is what she wrote.

21:34.679 --> 21:35.640
I think we have a picture of it.

21:35.740 --> 21:36.882
This is inside of her Bible.

21:37.403 --> 21:39.105
February 12, 1997.

21:40.226 --> 21:40.987
Didn't even know her.

21:42.188 --> 21:45.893
I believe God has called me to be a pastor's wife.

21:45.913 --> 21:46.714
Isn't that crazy?

21:48.436 --> 21:50.098
Listen, that's unbelievable.

21:51.920 --> 21:53.021
She was looking for me.

21:53.062 --> 21:54.123
I was looking for her.

21:54.163 --> 21:55.625
We didn't even know each other.

21:56.285 --> 22:00.050
Look, I didn't decide to become a pastor until I graduated from Liberty.

22:00.290 --> 22:04.702
I didn't even, she knew I was gonna be a pastor before I knew I was gonna be a pastor, at least crazy.

22:05.524 --> 22:08.592
Here's what I'm saying, you attract who you are.

22:08.953 --> 22:14.066
If you wanna find the right person, work on your heart and all the married people said.

22:14.882 --> 22:17.987
Amen, a little louder, amen, to the single people.

22:18.227 --> 22:20.711
Now, let's talk to you married folk, because we're all screwed up, okay?

22:21.132 --> 22:22.033
We're all messed up.

22:22.314 --> 22:24.037
We want to fix our spouse.

22:24.077 --> 22:24.818
They're the problem.

22:24.858 --> 22:28.203
I get emails all the time, Pastor Danny, my husband, blah, blah, blah.

22:28.223 --> 22:28.864
How do I fix them?

22:29.185 --> 22:30.687
My wife, blah, blah, blah, blah.

22:30.707 --> 22:31.509
How do I fix her?

22:31.789 --> 22:32.751
It's all I get them all the time.

22:33.852 --> 22:36.196
Here's the hard truth that you need to hear today.

22:36.316 --> 22:38.720
You can't fix anybody, so chill out.

22:39.381 --> 22:42.386
Stop sending me emails about how to fix your spouse.

22:42.690 --> 22:44.894
You can email me, just not about that, okay?

22:45.314 --> 22:47.838
Because you cannot fix them, okay?

22:47.858 --> 22:50.663
Let me go back to the single people really quick and we'll jump back to the married people.

22:50.923 --> 23:02.923
If you're dating and you realize there's all kinds of things in this girl's life, all kinds of things in this guy's life that are broken, listen, divorce them, divorce them.

23:03.224 --> 23:09.554
The greatest, I heard this from a friend of mine years ago, the greatest divorce is the one that happens before the wedding, okay?

23:10.242 --> 23:10.883
Break it off.

23:11.203 --> 23:16.229
Do not move forward if he or she is unwilling to resolve some of those issues on their own.

23:16.250 --> 23:17.511
Let's go back to the married folks.

23:18.152 --> 23:22.998
You can't fix anyone, but you can influence them.

23:24.380 --> 23:25.301
There's a big difference.

23:27.243 --> 23:28.224
You can influence them.

23:29.166 --> 23:34.693
Dr. Robert Mahal and Jr. wrote this statement, and I think it's brilliant.

23:35.393 --> 23:39.058
Spiritual growth is the process of being conformed to the image of Jesus,

23:39.330 --> 23:42.194
And we talk about that a lot at this church, what does spiritual growth look like?

23:42.594 --> 23:43.556
Becoming like Jesus.

23:44.617 --> 23:51.886
But it's this last little phrase that he added that caught my attention for the sake of others.

23:52.988 --> 24:00.017
Your spiritual growth, my spiritual growth, my conformity to Christ, putting on the character of Christ, your spiritual growth is not just for you.

24:00.998 --> 24:05.604
Do you get to experience joy and peace and contentment and satisfaction and fulfillment and freedom from sin?

24:05.684 --> 24:06.866
Yeah, absolutely.

24:07.650 --> 24:09.091
But there are beneficiaries of that.

24:09.111 --> 24:10.192
You know who the beneficiary is?

24:10.272 --> 24:11.874
The closest person to you.

24:11.934 --> 24:18.380
And for the married folks in this room today, and for those watching everywhere else at our locations, that's your spouse.

24:20.122 --> 24:23.905
Your spiritual growth is for your spouse.

24:23.945 --> 24:25.547
It got me thinking about the fruit of the spirit.

24:26.007 --> 24:27.269
Talking about fruit today.

24:27.289 --> 24:27.769
A lot of fruit.

24:27.829 --> 24:29.090
Love, joy, peace, patience.

24:29.130 --> 24:30.672
Listen to what Paul says in Galatians 5.

24:31.773 --> 24:35.797
But the Holy Spirit produces this kind of fruit in our lives.

24:35.897 --> 24:37.138
Love, joy, peace.

24:38.210 --> 24:42.814
patience and kindness and faith goodness and faithfulness and gentleness and self-control.

24:42.954 --> 24:46.438
This is not an exhaustive list, but this is a pretty good list.

24:46.458 --> 24:50.842
These are attributes of Jesus' character.

24:50.942 --> 25:03.053
And when we stay connected to the Spirit and the Spirit of God is flowing in us and working in us and transforming us, we are able to demonstrate the same character of Jesus, love and joy and peace and patience and kindness and goodness and faithfulness and gentleness and self-control.

25:03.354 --> 25:07.858
What's interesting about this list is that almost all of these

25:08.034 --> 25:11.078
really only makes sense in the context of a relationship.

25:11.118 --> 25:12.019
I mean, look with me at these.

25:12.100 --> 25:16.386
What does love really mean if there's no object to be loved?

25:16.406 --> 25:18.929
No person to be loved, right?

25:19.470 --> 25:23.275
Like, love only makes sense when there's a relationship with another individual.

25:23.355 --> 25:24.857
I do what is best for them.

25:25.098 --> 25:26.419
You do what is best for them.

25:26.820 --> 25:27.641
You think about peace.

25:27.661 --> 25:31.186
I mean, you can have inner peace by yourself, but most of the time, peace makes sense.

25:31.246 --> 25:34.310
But in the context of a relationship, what about patience?

25:34.350 --> 25:35.532
That's the most important one.

25:35.552 --> 25:37.074
Maybe, maybe not.

25:37.570 --> 26:00.946
Patience what patience what is patience mean outside of the context of who you're gonna be patient with right just this morning You know I tell my kids to put their shoes away put their shoes away put their shoes away a million times put their shoes away right and I go outside this morning in the garage and there's shoes that are not on the On the rack the rack is here and the shoes are on the floor here Help me help me do you understand do you do empathize?

26:01.762 --> 26:10.157
So this morning I lost my patience and I grabbed all the shoes and threw them all the way across the garage like I told my children that I would.

26:10.557 --> 26:13.162
And now thankfully I didn't do it in anger this time.

26:13.422 --> 26:14.104
I did it in love.

26:16.648 --> 26:20.214
Because I want what's best for them and what's best for them is to put their shoes on the rack.

26:20.455 --> 26:21.857
You see I'm making progress here.

26:23.741 --> 26:24.562
Patience.

26:25.378 --> 26:27.281
What is kindness outside the context of her?

26:27.421 --> 26:28.442
Who are you gonna be kind to?

26:28.482 --> 26:31.427
I mean, you could be kind to yourself, but look at this, gentleness.

26:31.647 --> 26:34.892
What does gentleness mean outside of the context of a relationship, right?

26:34.912 --> 26:41.621
All of these character traits or attributes only really make the full sense in the context of a relationship or marriage.

26:42.162 --> 26:43.464
Here's what I'm saying.

26:43.484 --> 26:53.458
If spiritual growth is not just for you, it's if it's for the other person, then the more I work on producing this kind of fruit in my life, guess who gets to eat it?

26:54.626 --> 26:57.429
Your wife, your husband.

26:59.132 --> 27:11.006
And yes, other people, if you happen to have other people living in your home, but first and foremost, your wife, listen, the more we grow spiritually, the more we influence our spouse.

27:12.028 --> 27:20.057
What if Jesus were to come to your house and tap on your children, say, take a break, I'll live with him for two months?

27:22.661 --> 27:23.762
What if you were to tap on your,

27:23.970 --> 27:24.290
Get out.

27:24.491 --> 27:25.552
I'll live with her.

27:25.833 --> 27:32.603
Do you think that if Jesus lived with your wife for two months that he would influence her in a positive way?

27:32.663 --> 27:34.306
Yes or no?

27:34.326 --> 27:38.011
Do you think if Jesus were to walk in and live with your husband for two months?

27:38.051 --> 27:40.956
Hey, it wouldn't even take that long.

27:40.976 --> 27:44.942
A month and demonstrate this kind of fruit to your husband.

27:45.242 --> 27:46.804
Do you think that it would influence him?

27:47.325 --> 27:47.826
Yes or no?

27:48.866 --> 27:51.550
See, we can't change people, but we can influence them.

27:51.810 --> 28:00.862
There's a passage in the book of 2 Peter, chapter one, Peter says, hey, you wives, I want you to, this isn't very popular today, but I want you to submit yourselves to your husbands.

28:00.902 --> 28:02.384
I want you to come into their authority.

28:02.645 --> 28:05.729
I want you to listen to them and honor them.

28:06.149 --> 28:18.386
If you do this, ladies, watch this, then even if some refuse to believe the good news, even if they're not believers in Jesus, your godly lives will speak to them without any words.

28:20.066 --> 28:21.969
And some of you men are like, man, that'd be nice.

28:24.993 --> 28:26.035
They talk a lot, don't they?

28:28.639 --> 28:29.660
I'm for you guys.

28:29.760 --> 28:30.201
I'm for you.

28:30.221 --> 28:30.662
I feel you.

28:30.802 --> 28:31.363
I feel your pain.

28:34.347 --> 28:35.469
What is Peter saying here?

28:35.569 --> 28:38.834
Listen, listen to the next phrase.

28:38.978 --> 28:39.779
one over.

28:39.859 --> 28:40.019
Who?

28:40.200 --> 28:42.163
These husbands who don't even believe in Jesus.

28:42.643 --> 28:43.885
They will be one over.

28:44.085 --> 28:44.946
They will change.

28:45.127 --> 28:48.932
They will be influenced by observing your pure and reverent lives.

28:49.132 --> 28:56.082
Not by hearing you in their ear all day, but just by watching your reverent, godly life, they will be one over.

28:56.223 --> 28:59.407
Listen, this isn't even a message to the women today.

28:59.427 --> 29:01.490
This is a message to all of us who are married.

29:02.082 --> 29:09.929
Stop talking husbands, stop talking wives, and just work on the tree and let the fruit come, and your spouse will be one over.

29:10.550 --> 29:11.451
Can you say this with me?

29:12.512 --> 29:15.074
One over, come on, all of our locations, ready?

29:15.815 --> 29:26.605
One over, not by our words, not by anger, not by threats, but by watching the fruit blossom from the tree.

29:27.767 --> 29:28.627
And they'll be influenced.

29:28.667 --> 29:30.169
So how do we fix our marriages?

29:30.309 --> 29:31.410
We work on ourselves.

29:31.490 --> 29:33.373
We become the right person.

29:33.393 --> 29:35.256
Now the question is, how do I become the right person?

29:35.276 --> 29:38.742
Great, okay, it's gonna help me find the right person if I become the right person.

29:38.762 --> 29:41.666
It's gonna help me fix my marriage problems if I have marriage problems.

29:41.927 --> 29:42.929
But how do I do that?

29:42.949 --> 29:44.812
Well, Jesus did not leave us out in the cold.

29:44.852 --> 29:51.743
Listen to what he said in John 15, remain in me and I will remain in you for a branch cannot produce fruit.

29:51.903 --> 29:53.105
I hear again, we're talking about fruit.

29:53.886 --> 29:58.674
If it's severed from the vine and you cannot be fruitful unless you say it with me,

29:58.978 --> 30:00.500
Remain in me.

30:00.560 --> 30:02.021
Then he continues in verse five.

30:02.202 --> 30:07.127
Yes, I am the true vine or the trunk of the tree and you are the branches.

30:07.828 --> 30:19.080
Those branches that sit with me remain a little bit louder, remain or stay connected or stay attached in me and I in them, those branches will produce much fruit.

30:19.461 --> 30:26.789
But if you become detached, if you separate from the trunk for apart from me, you can do nothing.

30:26.809 --> 30:27.730
There'll be no fruit.

30:28.386 --> 30:39.318
The only thing your spouse will get is the works of the flesh, anger, jealousy, bitterness, resentment, lack of forgiveness, which is human.

30:41.801 --> 30:44.043
How do we fix our marriage problems?

30:44.984 --> 30:45.565
We remain.

30:46.246 --> 30:47.587
We stay connected to Jesus.

30:48.348 --> 30:57.298
And then what happens is the supernatural sap that's in the trunk will flow from the trunk into the branch, which is you and I, and the fruit will come.

30:57.826 --> 31:02.815
Whatever fruit is needed, our job is to remain.

31:02.875 --> 31:10.248
The best advice that I've ever given myself when it comes to my marriage is very simple, and that's to remain in Jesus.

31:11.470 --> 31:16.018
If I have marriage problems, the answer every single time, no matter what it is,

31:16.738 --> 31:20.362
It's to remain in Jesus, because if I remain in Jesus, I'm gonna find the patience that I need.

31:20.622 --> 31:23.045
If I remain in Jesus, I'm gonna find the ability to be gentle.

31:23.285 --> 31:25.608
If I remain in Jesus, I'm gonna find the ability to humble myself.

31:25.848 --> 31:28.491
If I remain in Jesus, I'm gonna find the ability to love my wife.

31:28.731 --> 31:32.795
If I remain, it's all about remaining, staying attached.

31:32.815 --> 31:33.716
How do you do that?

31:33.836 --> 31:34.437
How do you do that?

31:34.477 --> 31:35.919
Well, there's a hundred ways to do it.

31:36.579 --> 31:43.807
This actually is one of the hundred ways to stay, to be attached, or to remain, to be in church and to hear the word of God.

31:43.827 --> 31:46.450
It helps us, but there's 99 others.

31:47.042 --> 31:53.489
You could remain in Jesus by going out and taking a walk in the outside and saying, God, the heavens declare the glory of God.

31:53.509 --> 31:55.852
And I attached to you by being in nature.

31:56.893 --> 32:01.158
You can practice silence and solitude and prayer and attach to Jesus that way.

32:01.598 --> 32:02.820
There are hundreds of things.

32:02.840 --> 32:05.042
You can listen to worship music as you work out.

32:05.262 --> 32:08.986
And as you're working out your body, your soul is remaining in Christ.

32:09.307 --> 32:11.049
Last week, I talked about meditation.

32:11.429 --> 32:12.651
Haha, were you there for that?

32:12.891 --> 32:13.532
That was a great word.

32:14.352 --> 32:15.794
It means to meditate.

32:16.130 --> 32:18.032
This is probably the most important one.

32:18.072 --> 32:25.101
Throughout the day, I will just take verses in my head that I've meditated on and I'll just go over them and recite them right in the middle of the day.

32:25.341 --> 32:28.245
One of my favorite things to do is to take Psalm 23.

32:28.525 --> 32:29.806
No matter where I am, I can do it.

32:30.087 --> 32:32.169
I'll do it right now for you and I can meditate on it.

32:32.470 --> 32:33.271
This is what it says.

32:34.372 --> 32:35.393
But the Lord is my shepherd.

32:35.794 --> 32:36.474
I shall not want.

32:37.396 --> 32:39.058
He makes me lie down in green pastures.

32:39.358 --> 32:40.920
He leads me besides still waters.

32:40.940 --> 32:42.342
He restores my soul.

32:43.243 --> 32:46.066
He leads me in paths of righteousness for his namesake.

32:46.466 --> 32:49.711
And even though I walk through the valley of the shadow of death, I will fear no evil.

32:49.951 --> 32:50.913
For you are with me.

32:50.953 --> 32:52.916
Your rod and your staff, they comfort me.

32:54.117 --> 32:56.481
You prepare a table before me in the presence of my enemies.

32:56.521 --> 32:57.683
You anoint my head with oil.

32:58.003 --> 32:59.205
My cup runs over.

33:00.126 --> 33:02.910
Surely goodness and mercy shall follow me all the days of my life.

33:03.351 --> 33:04.953
And I will dwell in the house of the Lord forever.

33:04.973 --> 33:05.775
And I'll just say that.

33:07.517 --> 33:10.802
And as soon as I get my mind on Psalm 23,

33:11.074 --> 33:13.358
Connection, attachment, remaining.

33:13.398 --> 33:16.663
And the sap from the branch flows through into the vine.

33:16.864 --> 33:19.608
And the fruit that I need for that moment comes.

33:20.069 --> 33:22.393
Remain, remain, remain.

33:22.413 --> 33:23.234
Is this making sense?

33:23.775 --> 33:24.276
Attach.

33:26.159 --> 33:31.628
Years ago when I was dating Jackie, we made a commitment not to be intimate until our wedding night.

33:32.149 --> 33:33.150
And that's what the Bible says.

33:33.251 --> 33:34.473
And we said, look, we're going to follow.

33:34.733 --> 33:35.775
We're followers of Jesus.

33:36.075 --> 33:37.778
We're faithful.

33:38.370 --> 33:40.693
And so what that meant was that she couldn't stay the night.

33:40.773 --> 33:44.899
I had my own apartment at Liberty, and there was really no supervision.

33:44.939 --> 33:46.181
It was just God and us.

33:47.302 --> 33:50.407
So if we were going to stay pure, there was no one there to check us.

33:51.628 --> 33:56.075
And so around 11 o'clock, 11 30, 12 o'clock at night, she would have to leave.

33:56.595 --> 33:59.740
Because if she didn't leave, it wouldn't have been good.

34:00.821 --> 34:01.823
She could not stay the night.

34:03.084 --> 34:05.828
And every time she left, listen, she had a diamond ring.

34:06.029 --> 34:07.090
We were engaged.

34:07.490 --> 34:09.092
It was like, come on, this is a slam dunk.

34:09.153 --> 34:10.475
I'm practically already married.

34:10.535 --> 34:11.476
Can't we just have sex?

34:11.636 --> 34:11.917
No.

34:13.119 --> 34:15.422
So she would leave and I would be, oh man, don't leave.

34:16.624 --> 34:17.065
But she did.

34:17.806 --> 34:21.612
And we were faithful until our wedding night.

34:23.074 --> 34:25.278
And on August 14, 1999, we stayed.

34:26.700 --> 34:30.706
And we stayed a lot.

34:37.090 --> 34:37.951
And we still stay.

34:37.991 --> 34:42.195
And this isn't about sex or anything like that.

34:42.615 --> 34:46.839
But just the fact, come back with me, come back with me.

34:48.841 --> 34:55.067
Just the fact that from that point on August 14, 1999, she did not have to leave.

34:56.608 --> 34:57.289
We stayed.

34:57.349 --> 34:59.051
You know what it means to remain?

34:59.091 --> 35:00.392
It just means to be with.

35:01.513 --> 35:04.215
What if you could create rhythms in life?

35:05.897 --> 35:07.058
And this is really the goal.

35:07.170 --> 35:08.511
of being a follower of Christ.

35:08.531 --> 35:18.301
What if you could create rhythms in life, practices, and habits that would allow you to stay in the presence of Jesus no matter where you are, no matter what group of friends you're with.

35:19.842 --> 35:29.732
If you're in a movie, if you're in a gym, a coffee shop, Kroger shopping, at home by yourself, what if you could create rhythms where you're just with Jesus all the time?

35:31.414 --> 35:32.174
Or you're remaining.

35:33.416 --> 35:35.858
I promise you, the fruit will come.

35:36.930 --> 35:38.972
And it'll bless your relationships.

35:39.492 --> 35:48.381
You'll have the character traits and the attributes you need for that relationship, whatever they are, strength, fortitude, courage, forgiveness, love.

35:49.722 --> 35:53.706
And you will draw the type of person who's looking for that type of fruit in their life.

35:53.946 --> 35:58.691
I promise you, be the right person by remaining in Jesus.

35:59.191 --> 36:00.612
Now, there's some of you here today.

36:00.652 --> 36:03.735
You need to take that first initial step.

36:04.116 --> 36:06.578
Jesus would say to you, you're not yet in the kingdom.

36:07.458 --> 36:09.380
you're not yet one of my followers.

36:09.641 --> 36:16.729
And he would invite you in, he would say to you today, if he were here, look, I died on the cross to remove any barrier between you and I.

36:16.970 --> 36:23.818
Like I wanna live with you, I wanna dwell with you, I wanna empower you, I wanna put my strength in you, my peace in you, my joy in you.

36:24.079 --> 36:30.506
Yes, I wanna take you to heaven when you die, but I want you to live in abundant, powerful, beautiful, supernatural life right now.

36:32.129 --> 36:36.594
And some of you need to do that, and you haven't, and you've been waiting,

36:36.802 --> 36:37.964
because you think it's about religion.

36:38.144 --> 36:39.706
This is not about religion.

36:39.926 --> 36:41.448
This is not about church.

36:41.749 --> 36:47.256
This is not a set of rules that you're gonna, this is about you and God entering into fellowship.

36:49.099 --> 36:49.600
Would you come?

36:50.481 --> 36:51.763
Would you place your faith in Christ?

36:51.803 --> 36:53.405
Would you trust Him to forgive your sins?

36:54.286 --> 36:56.730
If that's where you're at right now, I'm gonna say a simple prayer.

36:56.910 --> 37:03.118
And I encourage you, if you haven't done this, to take this step right now, this is your moment in time.

37:04.040 --> 37:05.682
It's created for you.

37:06.754 --> 37:11.541
Move and step and reach in faith and trust Christ today.

37:11.561 --> 37:12.963
Will you pray with me if you feel led to?

37:15.087 --> 37:15.828
Just say this to him.

37:15.848 --> 37:16.709
It's not about the words.

37:16.789 --> 37:18.292
It's about the faith behind the words.

37:21.236 --> 37:28.467
Dear Jesus, I reach out to you with what little faith I have.

37:28.487 --> 37:32.373
And I trust you.

37:34.176 --> 37:35.538
I believe in my heart

37:37.122 --> 37:48.394
that you died for my son, to wash away the guilt and the shame and the penalty.

37:50.557 --> 37:57.805
Wash me today, cleanse my soul, fill me with your spirit.

38:00.087 --> 38:06.514
And from this day forward, teach me to remain in you.

38:07.554 --> 38:18.413
to stay attached, connected, so that my tree, my life, my soul, will bear good fruit.

38:18.433 --> 38:21.198
I pray this in Jesus' name.

38:21.218 --> 38:24.724
And everybody said, amen, amen, amen.

38:24.784 --> 38:25.685
God is at work.

38:26.527 --> 38:28.029
Come on, give him glory, amen.

38:29.873 --> 38:31.475
He is moving in powerful ways.

38:31.495 --> 38:32.978
Hey, if you trusted Christ,

38:33.218 --> 38:36.141
If you just prayed that prayer, we would love to hear from you.

38:36.161 --> 38:48.091
If you just grab your phone really quick and text the word saved to 65248, here's why we want to come behind you as your church and show you what the next steps are, whether that's getting in the group or getting baptized.

38:48.391 --> 38:49.472
So text the word saved.

38:49.532 --> 38:51.454
We also would like to put a gift in your hands.

38:51.814 --> 38:52.775
This is what it looks like.

38:52.815 --> 39:03.204
It's a little box from us to you inside as a Bible, a cup, a nice coffee cup from us, and also a reading plan with some help and on your next step in your journey with Christ.

39:03.184 --> 39:06.720
pick these up, whatever location you're at, they're in the back of the auditorium right there.

39:07.102 --> 39:12.306
One more time, church, can we give God glory, amen?

